The President has designated all funding designated by Congress in the Consolidated and Further Continuing Appropriations Act, 2015, as emergency requirements. This designation is in accordance with section 6 of the Act and section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. The letter is signed by President Barack Obama.